casebody.data:
Richards, Respondent, v. Richards, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. May 9, 1890.)

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

John A. Anderson, for appellant. Frank E. Blackwell, for respondent.

No opinion. On appellant’s paying $10 costs of motion, and stipulating to argue at next term of court, motion denied.
